article.headline: Georgia 77, ETSU 57
article.story:
ATHENS, Ga. --  Angel Robinson scored 19 points and Georgia romped to a 77-57 victory over East Tennessee State on Monday night for the 750th win in school history.

The Lady Bulldogs became the 10th NCAA Division I women's program to reach the milestone, improving to 750-311 in their 35-year history.

Ashley Houts added 13 points and Danielle Taylor 10 for the Lady Bulldogs (6-1). Ten Georgia players scored in the team's fourth game in six days.

The Lady Bulldogs never trailed, building a double-digit lead on Robinson's layup midway through the first half. Georgia was up 42-23 at halftime and stretched the margin as high as 27 late in the game.

East Tennessee State (1-4) shot just 30 percent (20 of 66) from the field. Devin Thompson led with 15 points, Latisha Belcher added 14 and Siarre Evans 10.
